Fix missing libgen.h include for basename() on macOS 26 (Tahoe)

From ae0b75c1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Boris Buliga <boris@d12frosted.io>
Date: Sun, 19 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add #include <libgen.h> for basename() declaration

Commit bc5fb19 (2026-01-17) "NS: Fix startup with HAVE_NATIVE_COMP &&
!NS_SELF_CONTAINED" added a call to basename() in pdumper.c without
including <libgen.h>, which declares it on POSIX systems.

On macOS 26 (Tahoe), this causes a build failure:

  pdumper.c:5653:15: error: use of undeclared identifier 'basename'

Adding <libgen.h> to the includes fixes the build.

* src/pdumper.c: Include libgen.h for basename().
---
 src/pdumper.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/pdumper.c b/src/pdumper.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/pdumper.c
+++ b/src/pdumper.c
@@ -24,6 +24,7 @@ along with GNU Emacs.  If not, see <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.  */
 #include <errno.h>
 #include <fcntl.h>
 #include <limits.h>
+#include <libgen.h>
 #include <math.h>
 #include <stdarg.h>
 #include <stdint.h>
